Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Warsaw Frederic Chopin Airport in Poland, where he thanked the members of the Armed Forces of Poland and the United States for their service and dedication to freedom. He expressed pride in the American troops deployed in Poland and acknowledged the service members from his home state of Indiana. Pence brought greetings from President Donald Trump and thanked Poland for its commitment to spending 2 percent of its GDP on defense. He highlighted the importance of NATO and the United States' commitment to its allies. Pence also announced an agreement for Poland to purchase High Mobility Artillery Rocket System launchers from the United States. He concluded his speech by expressing confidence in the military's readiness and commitment to protecting freedom and forging a future of security and peace.